se-itll-help-astronomers-investigate-a-cosmic-mystery-dark-energy-180988643/</link><description>暗能量光谱仪花了五年时间从亚利桑那州观测天空。现在，研究人员拥有大量数据来研究宇宙数十亿年来如何演化</description><pubDate>Fri, 01 May 2026 15:21:22 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-is-the-largest-most-detailed-3d-map-of-the-universe-itll-help-astronomers-investigate-a-cosmic-mystery-dark-energy-180988643/</guid></item><item><title>如何从 261 年前建造的破纪录战舰上举起一根 30,000 磅重的桅杆？拥有一台非常非常大的起重机</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/how-do-you-lift-a-30000-pound-mast-from-a-warship-built-a-record-breaking-261-years-ago-with-a-really-really-big-crane-180988658/</link><description>英国皇家海军“胜利”号曾参加过美国独立战争、法国独立战争和拿破仑战争。这是世界上最古老的军舰，仍在服役，但急需维修</description><pubDate>Fri, 01 May 2026 15:00:20 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/how-do-you-lift-a-30000-pound-mast-from-a-warship-built-a-record-breaking-261-years-ago-with-a-really-really-big-crane-180988658/</guid></item><item><title>亚历山大大帝的（大理石）头像出现在纽约。美国官员称其被盗并刚刚送回意大利</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/alexander-the-greats-marble-head-turned-up-in-new-york-us-officials-say-it-was-stolen-and-just-sent-it-back-to-italy-180988650/</link><description>作为帮助意大利寻找失踪宝藏的长期努力的一部分，美国本周归还了数百件古代考古发现</description><pubDate>Thu, 30 Apr 2026 20:57:19 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/alexander-the-greats-marble-head-turned-up-in-new-york-us-officials-say-it-was-stolen-and-just-sent-it-back-to-italy-180988650/</guid></item><item><title>一名男子和他的狗在英格兰一处古老森林中散步时发现了一个 3,400 年前的斧头</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-man-and-his-dog-accidentally-discovered-a-3400-year-old-ax-head-while-out-for-a-walk-in-one-of-englands-ancient-forests-180988649/</link><description>研究人员认为，这把斧头的历史可以追溯到公元前 1400 年至公元前 1275 年之间，是青铜时代的遗物，当时人类开始使用金属</description><pubDate>Thu, 30 Apr 2026 18:45:57 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-man-and-his-dog-accidentally-discovered-a-3400-year-old-ax-head-while-out-for-a-walk-in-one-of-englands-ancient-forests-180988649/</guid></item><item><title>澳大利亚的松露产业非常成功。这项新研究可以解释原因</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/australia-has-a-surprisingly-successful-truffle-industry-this-new-study-could-explain-why-180988653/</link><description>研究人员检查了数百个土壤样本，以揭示为什么昂贵的真菌在该国蓬勃发展</description><pubDate>Thu, 30 Apr 2026 17:43:43 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/australia-has-a-surprisingly-successful-truffle-industry-this-new-study-could-explain-why-180988653/</guid></item><item><title>研究人员发现了一首失落的最古老英语诗歌，由 1,300 多年前不识字的牛郎创作</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/researchers-discovered-a-lost-copy-of-the-oldest-english-poem-composed-by-an-illiterate-cowherd-more-than-1300-years-ago-180988644/</link><description>这个版本的“Caedmon&amp;#39;s Hymn”展示了古英语是如何演变的。它还早期使用了当今英语读者认为理所当然的标点符号——句号——但不是以预期的方式使用</description><pubDate>Thu, 30 Apr 2026 15:39:39 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/researchers-discovered-a-lost-copy-of-the-oldest-english-poem-composed-by-an-illiterate-cowherd-more-than-1300-years-ago-180988644/</guid></item><item><title>当维苏威火山爆发时，这个人逃离了庞贝城。 2000年后，考古学家发现了他，手上拿着一个碗来保护他的头，一盏灯来照亮他的路</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-man-fled-pompeii-as-mount-vesuvius-erupted-archaeologists-found-him-2000-years-later-holding-a-bowl-to-protect-his-head-and-a-lamp-to-light-his-way-180988647/</link><description>最近的挖掘工作在古城墙外发现了两具骸骨。研究人员还对受害者悲惨的最后时刻之一进行了人工智能生成的重建</description><pubDate>Thu, 30 Apr 2026 15:10:21 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-man-fled-pompeii-as-mount-vesuvius-erupted-archaeologists-found-him-2000-years-later-holding-a-bowl-to-protect-his-head-and-a-lamp-to-light-his-way-180988647/</guid></item><item><title>两名运动员在两小时内跑完 26.2 英里，打破了马拉松里程碑。这是他们成就背后的科学原理</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/two-athletes-smashed-a-marathon-milestone-running-26-2-miles-in-under-two-hours-heres-the-science-behind-their-achievements-180988646/</link><description>高强度的训练方案、良好的天气条件、生理条件和轻便的鞋子可能是他们在周日伦敦马拉松比赛中取得惊人表现的原因之一</description><pubDate>Thu, 30 Apr 2026 14:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/two-athletes-smashed-a-marathon-milestone-running-26-2-miles-in-under-two-hours-heres-the-science-behind-their-achievements-180988646/</guid></item><item><title>一位金属探测器偶然发现了一枚银币。原来它是维京入侵英国期间埋藏的藏品的一部分</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-metal-detectorist-stumbled-upon-a-silver-coin-it-turned-out-to-be-part-of-a-stash-buried-during-the-viking-invasion-of-britain-180988645/</link><description>考古学家表示，这 63 枚硬币（其中大部分都以麦西亚国王伯格雷德的名字命名）可能在 9 世纪就被隐藏起来，以确保它们在动乱时期的安全</description><pubDate>Thu, 30 Apr 2026 12:42:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-metal-detectorist-stumbled-upon-a-silver-coin-it-turned-out-to-be-part-of-a-stash-buried-during-the-viking-invasion-of-britain-180988645/</guid></item><item><title>一对父女伪造了沃霍尔、班克斯、毕加索等人的 200 多件艺术品，并以 200 万美元的价格出售</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-father-and-daughter-forged-more-than-200-artworks-by-warhol-banksy-picasso-and-others-and-old-them-for-2-million-180988641/</link><description>新泽西州的居民委托波兰的一位艺术家制作这些赝品，他们将面临最高 20 年的监禁。他们因伪造美洲原住民艺术家的画作而受到特别处罚</description><pubDate>Wed, 29 Apr 2026 21:26:09 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-father-and-daughter-forged-more-than-200-artworks-by-warhol-banksy-picasso-and-others-and-old-them-for-2-million-180988641/</guid></item><item><title>科学家们绘制了小鼠鼻子中第一张详细的气味传感器“气味图”，并嗅出了一些令人惊讶的发现</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/scientists-create-the-first-detailed-smell-map-of-odor-sensors-in-the-mouse-nose-and-sniff-out-some-surprises-180988639/</link><description>在两项新研究中，研究人员利用遗传技术推翻了长期以来的假设，即带有气味探测器的神经细胞是随机排列的。他们不知道人类鼻子中是否也存在相同的空间组织</description><pubDate>Wed, 29 Apr 2026 20:59:40 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/scientists-create-the-first-detailed-smell-map-of-odor-sensors-in-the-mouse-nose-and-sniff-out-some-surprises-180988639/</guid></item><item><title>这些建筑物和桥梁是英格兰和威尔士最“濒危”的建筑和桥梁，它们告诉我们很多关于维多利亚时代生活的信息</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/these-buildings-and-bridges-are-the-most-endangered-in-england-and-wales-and-they-tell-us-a-lot-about-life-in-the-victorian-era-180988642/</link><description>大英帝国鼎盛时期遗留下来的建筑揭示了 1800 年代和 1900 年代初不断变化的经济、医疗和教育趋势。但由于年久失修，他们的遗产正面临风险</description><pubDate>Wed, 29 Apr 2026 19:41:34 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/these-buildings-and-bridges-are-the-most-endangered-in-england-and-wales-and-they-tell-us-a-lot-about-life-in-the-victorian-era-180988642/</guid></item><item><title>FDA 批准首个耳聋基因疗法，旨在恢复患有罕见遗传性疾病的儿童的听力</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-fda-approves-the-first-ever-gene-therapy-for-deafness-which-aims-to-restore-hearing-in-kids-with-a-rare-inherited-condition-180988635/</link><description>该机构的决定是基于一项临床试验的结果，在该试验中，该治疗改善了 80% 儿科参与者的听力。然而，聋人社区倡导者对治愈听力损失的努力感到担忧</description><pubDate>Wed, 29 Apr 2026 17:44:40 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-fda-approves-the-first-ever-gene-therapy-for-deafness-which-aims-to-restore-hearing-in-kids-with-a-rare-inherited-condition-180988635/</guid></item><item><title>一位浮潜生物学家在野外拍摄了第一张新孵化的加州大鲵的照片。这就是为什么这很重要</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-snorkeling-biologist-snapped-the-first-ever-photos-of-newly-hatched-california-giant-salamanders-in-the-wild-heres-why-thats-a-big-deal-180988619/</link><description>这一发现提供了关于一个鲜为人知的物种的另一个关键数据点，对于该物种来说，每一次观察都很重要</description><pubDate>Wed, 29 Apr 2026 17:16:41 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-snorkeling-biologist-snapped-the-first-ever-photos-of-newly-hatched-california-giant-salamanders-in-the-wild-heres-why-thats-a-big-deal-180988619/</guid></item></channel></rss>